CAF's next poll is scheduled to take place in March 2021 in Ethiopia, where the Malagasy stunningly dethroned long-standing leader, Issa Hayatou in 2017. Ahmad, the subject of an ongoing FIFA ethics case, indicated that he is likely to decide later on and only after seeking guidance from colleagues. "I still take advice from all the participating parties of African football," the FIFA Vice-President told BBC Sport Africa. "Once it's done, I'll be able to say whether or not I go for it." --BBC--